reviews.review_text:
the one thank you "cosmic" charlie for putting this board on . The sound is a lot better than on the audience copy. 
if IT's NOT A GREAT SHOW, it's a good show with a nice set list and some good jams. 
I would always remember the feeling of being  a part of the audience inside soldier field that nite, clapping and singing a long not fade away with more than 50 000 people, it changed my life.
GRETTINGS FROM MARSEILLE
Storms Lightning hit Soldier Field that nite right before the show and they cleared the infield for awhile.  Sting didn't come out but the Dead naturally did.

dwarvish fingers My third Dead show, but the first which I really dug into.  That was quite a summer.

During Peggy-O I remember imagining an army of dwarves taking over a castle, walking step by step, very slowly, without fighting, just walking.

It's funny how Loose Lucy falls apart.

Crazy Fingers was another highlight for me.

ps. the Sting/storm stuff was from 93 - I remember feeling grumpy about the rain, and then the Dead played "Rain" and I felt embarrassed.

My second and final show I remember Jerry forgetting the words in Uncle Johns, and the Loose Lucy debacle. I do not remember a lightning strike but I am sure it happened. It all seems like a vague dream now.
A pretty good show I'd say, interesting set list as others have mentioned.
Hello from Texas

Wharf Rat There's not a whole lot good one can say about summer tour '92.  I will say that the Wharf Rat from this show was one of the highlights of the 8-10 shows I saw that summer.  The jam out of Wharf Rat really salvaged the trip all the way up to Chicago for me.

Wharf Rat Jerry's passion in this Wharf Rat is nice to hear again and so clearly!

Thanks again Charlie and Co... :)

Night 2 at Soldier Field, Su92 Underwhelming after the buzz and excitement of the night prior at Soldier Field. Still a fair show for 92. This last week of the run, from roughly mid-June to the end of the month, is perhaps among the year's best. By this point, of course, Jerry was exhausted. He'd collapse, again, shortly after from exhaustion and the fall tour would be cancelled. Next show after the tour finale on 7/1 is 12/2/92. Chicago return comes sp93 for an excellent three-night run at the Rosement. Listen!
